David BAER, Respondent,
v.
Teresa BAER, Appellant. No. ED 105289 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION THREE. Filed: February 27, 2018 Lawrence G. Gillespie, 120 South Central Avenue, Suite 650, Clayton, MO 63105, Julie K.H. McCarver, 307 E. Karsch Blvd., P.O. Box 790, Farmington, MO 63640, for Appellant. Suzan Kay Ponder-Bates, P.O. Box 99, Festus, MO 63028, Thomas P. Duggan, Jr., 1001 Main Street, P.O. Box 909, Imperial, MO 63052, Respondent. Before Gary M. Gaertner, Jr., P.J., Robert M. Clayton III, J., Angela T. Quigless, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM.

Teresa Baer appeals the judgment denying her motion to set aside the judgment dissolving her marriage to David Baer. We find no error has occurred.

No jurisprudential purpose would be served by a written opinion. We have, however, provided the parties a memorandum setting forth the reasons for our decision. The judgment of the trial court is affirmed under Rule 84.16(b).
